data.description: This lovely townhome, situated in the heart of downtown Lambertville, is a beautiful example of historic charm. Built in 1860, it boasts a bright and vibrant brick exterior, complete with a charming front patio. The interior is equally inviting, with a cozy living room featuring a gas stove and rich hardwood floors that extend throughout the home. The renovated kitchen, with its espresso maple cabinetry, granite countertops, and stainless-steel appliances, is the perfect space for cooking and entertaining. The step-down living/dining/recreation room is another highlight, featuring a sliding door that leads to the  soon to be new deck and views of Swan Creek. Upstairs, you'll find three spacious bedrooms and a renovated full bath, while the basement level provides ample storage space, full stone foundation, and access to the yard. Located in the popular weekend destination of Lambertville, this townhome offers an easy commute to many locations in the Northeast, with Manhattan approximately 90 minutes away and Philadelphia 60 minutes away. Enjoy fine dining, shopping, antiquing, and festivals on both sides of the Delaware River in this charming townhome. As is sale.
